<DIV1 TYPE="title page">
<PB REF="015714_0003_0F99DC3641B20948">
<P>THE COMPLAINT; OR NIGHT-THOUGHTS ON LIFE, DEATH, AND IMMORTALITY.</P>
<P>BY THE REVEREND EDWARD YOUNG, L L. D.</P>
<P>TO WHICH ARE ADDED, A POETICAL PARAPHRASE ON PART OF THE BOOK OF JOB; AND HIS POEM ON THE LAST DAY.</P>
<Q><L>Of man's employs, the greate&s;t &s;hould be this,</L>
<L>To find the road to&mdash;EVERLASTING BLISS;</L>
<L>To aid the Chri&s;tian who'd not walk in vain,</L>
<L>Here marks are fix'd to make the journey plain.</L>
<L>Read then this work, the path is plainly &s;hewn,</L>
<L>The &s;teps directed, and the way made known.</L>
<BIBL>FLEETWOOD</BIBL></Q>
<P><HI>PHILADELPHIA:</HI> Printed and Sold by ROBERT BELL, in <HI>Third-Street.</HI> MDCCLXXVII.</P>
