<L>Did&s;t &s;tain the cro&s;s; and, work of wonders far</L>
<L>The greate&s;t, that thy deare&s;t far might bleed.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>Bold thought! Shall I dare &s;peak it, or repre&s;s?</L>
<L>Should man more execrate, or boa&s;t, the guilt</L>
<L>Which rous'd &s;uch vengeance? which &s;uch love inflam'd?</L>
<L>O'er guilt (how mountainous!) with out &s;tretcht arms,</L>
<L>Stern ju&s;tice, and &s;oft-&s;miling love, embrace,</L>
<L>Supporting, in full maje&s;ty, thy throne,</L>
<L>When &s;eem'd its maje&s;ty to need &s;upport,</L>
<L>Or that, or man, inevitably lo&s;t:</L>
