<L>Pow'rs mo&s;t illumin'd, wilder'd in the theme.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>The theme, the joy, how then &s;hall man &s;u&s;tain?</L>
<L>Oh the bur&s;t gates! cru&s;h'd &s;ting! demoli&s;h'd throne!</L>
<L>La&s;t ga&s;p! of vanqui&s;h'd death. Shout earth and heav'n!</L>
<L>This &s;um of good to man. Who&s;e nature, then,</L>
<L><PB N="62" REF="015714_0067_0F99DC7BEC103A48">
Took wing, and mounted with him from the tomb?</L>
<L>Then, then, I ro&s;e; then fir&s;t humanity</L>
<L>Triumphant pa&s;t the cry&s;tal ports of light,</L>
