<L>And travel only gives us &s;ound repo&s;e.</L>
<L>Heav'n &s;ells all plea&s;ure; effort is the price:</L>
<L>The joys of conque&s;t, are the joys of man;</L>
<L>And glory the victorious laurel &s;preads</L>
<L>O'er plea&s;ure's pure, perpetual, placid &s;tream.</L>
<L>There is a time when toil mu&s;t be preferr'd,</L>
<L>Or joy, by mi&s;-tim'd fondne&s;s, is undone.</L>
<L>A man of plea&s;ure is a man of pains.</L>
