</LG>
<LG>
<L>Is joy the daughter of &s;everity?</L>
<L>It is:&mdash;Yet far my doctrine from &s;evere.</L>
<L>"Rejoice for ever;" it becomes a man;</L>
<L>Exalts and &s;ets him nearer to the Gods.</L>
<L>"Rejoice for ever." nature cries, "rejoice;"</L>
<L><PB N="207" REF="015714_0214_0F99E28C9542A468">
And drinks to man in her nectareous cup,</L>
<L>Mixt up of delicates for ev'ry &s;en&s;e;</L>
<L>To the great founder of the bounteous fea&s;t,</L>
<L>Drinks glory, gratitude, eternal prai&s;e;</L>
<L>And he that will not pledge her, is a churl.</L>
