<L>Her &s;acred int're&s;ts with the &s;trings of life.</L>
<L><PB N="208" REF="015714_0215_0F99E28DD9C45428">
Who breaks her aweful mandate, &s;hocks him&s;elf,</L>
<L>His better &s;elf: and is it greater pain,</L>
<L>Our &s;oul &s;hould murmur, or our du&s;t repine?</L>
<L>And one, in their eternal war, mu&s;t bleed.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>If one mo&s;t &s;uffer, which &s;hould lea&s;t be &s;par'd?</L>
<L>The pains of mind &s;urpa&s;s the pains of &s;en&s;e:</L>
<L>A&s;k, then, the gout, what torment is in guilt.</L>
