<LG>
<L>For what is vice? &s;elf-love in a mi&s;take:</L>
<L>A poor blind merchant buying joys too dear.</L>
<L><PB N="209" REF="015714_0216_0F99E28DE6C5DF70">
And virtue, what? 'tis &s;elf-love in her wits,</L>
<L>Quite &s;kilful in the market of delight.</L>
<L>Self-love's good &s;en&s;e is love of that dread power,</L>
<L>From whom her&s;elf, and all &s;he can enjoy.</L>
<L>Other &s;elf-love is but di&s;guis'd &s;elf-hate;</L>
<L>More mortal than the malice of our foes;</L>
<L>A &s;elf-hate, now &s;carce felt; then felt full-&s;ore,</L>
<L>When being, cur&s;t; extinction, loud implor'd;</L>
