<L>Con&s;i&s;tent wi&s;dom ever wills the &s;ame;</L>
<L>Thy fickle wi&s;h is ever on the wing.</L>
<L>Sick of her&s;elf, is folly's character.</L>
<L>As wi&s;dom's is, a mode&s;t &s;elf-applau&s;e.</L>
<L>A change of evils is thy good &s;upreme;</L>
<L>Nor, but in motion, can&s;t thou find thy re&s;t.</L>
<L>Man's greate&s;t &s;trength is &s;hewn in &s;tanding &s;till.</L>
<L><PB N="210" REF="015714_0217_0F99E28EA3F65838">
The fir&s;t &s;ure &s;ymptom of a mind in health,</L>
<L>Is re&s;t of heart, and plea&s;ure felt at home.</L>
<L>Fal&s;e plea&s;ure from abroad her joys imports;</L>
<L>Rich from within, and &s;elf-&s;u&s;tain'd, the true.</L>
