<L>A Seminary fraught with future Gods.</L>
<L>Nature all o'er is con&s;ecrated ground,</L>
<L>Teeming with growths immortal, and divine.</L>
<L>The great Proprietor's all-bounteous hand</L>
<L>Leaves nothing wa&s;te; but &s;ows the&s;e fiery fields</L>
<L>With Seeds of rea&s;on, which to virtues ri&s;e</L>
<L>Beneath his genial ray; and, if e&s;cap'd</L>
<L>The pe&s;tilential bla&s;ts of &s;tubborn will,</L>
<L>When grown mature, are gather'd for the &s;kies.</L>
