<L>That di&s;tant earth lies ba&s;king in the blaze?</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<PB N="302" REF="015714_0308_0F99E18FA1D9D908">
<L>Who did the Soul with her rich pow'rs inve&s;t,</L>
<L>And light up rea&s;on in the human brea&s;t?</L>
<L>To &s;hine, with fre&s;h increa&s;e of lu&s;tre, bright,</L>
<L>When &s;tars and &s;un are &s;et in endle&s;s night?</L>
<L>To the&s;e my various que&s;tions make reply.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>Th' Almighty &s;poke; and &s;peaking, &s;hook the &s;ky.</L>
<L>What then, Chaldaean Sire, was thy Surpri&s;e!</L>
<L>Thus thou, with trembling heart, and down ca&s;t eyes:</L>
<L>" Once and again, which I in groans deplore,</L>
<L>" My tongue has err'd; but &s;hall pre&s;ume no more.</L>
