<L>They ripen under his prolific ray.</L>
<L>Unmindful &s;he, that! &s;ome unhappy tread</L>
<L>May cru&s;h her young in their neglected bed.</L>
<L>What time &s;he &s;kims along the field with &s;peed,</L>
<L>She &s;corns the rider, and pur&s;uing &s;teed.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>How rich the Peacock! what bright glories run</L>
<L>From plume to plume, and vary in the &s;un!</L>
